## CONTENT STRUCTURE

**H1:** Short Old Money Nails: Classy Almond Designs That Work at Any Length

**H2 Structure:**

1. **Why Short Nails Are Actually the Most Authentic Old Money Look** *(reframe the premise — old money has always favoured short to mid-length; JFK Jr. references, Carolyn Bessette, Carolyn Kennedy; heritage women weren't flashing length)*
2. **What Shape Should You Choose for Short Old Money Nails?** *(almond is the ideal: elongates fingers, soft tapering; squoval for low-maintenance practicality; oval for sturdiness; what to avoid — coffin, stiletto, square with sharp corners)*
3. **Short Almond Nails That Look Old Money — Designs to Save** *(core design roundup: micro French, milky nude, sheer pink, burgundy, navy, espresso/mocha — image-led section with captions; anchor to image count)*
4. **The Colours That Look Expensive on Short Nails (and the Ones That Don't)** *(detailed colour guidance specific to shorter lengths — why some neutrals read plain at short length and others read polished; undertone guidance; link to old-money-nail-colors here)*
5. **Can You Do Old Money Nails Without Extensions?** *(yes — addresses the core anxiety; BIAB/gel overlay for strength and length; Russian manicure for perfect bed; discusses how the look is actually better natural)*
6. **What to Ask Your Nail Tech for Short Old Money Nails** *(exact language to use at salon; shape specifications; finish requirements; grooming details — cuticles, topcoat; makes reader feel confident before booking)*
7. **Short Old Money French Tip Nails — The Most Heritage Design** *(micro French and foggy French on short nails; baby boomer gradient; why thin tip is the old money rule; link to old-money-french-tip-nails contextually where natural)*
8. **Short Old Money Nails vs Short Quiet Luxury Nails: What's the Difference?** *(editorial distinction — same length philosophy, different heritage; old money is prep and JFK Jr. energy; quiet luxury is Succession-era stealth; link to short-quiet-luxury-nails)*
9. **How to Make Short Nails Look Polished Every Day — The Grooming Details That Matter** *(cuticle care, filing, topcoat frequency, chip-resistant finishes — the non-colour elements that separate groomed from forgettable)*

**Structure Reasoning:** The H2 order prioritises the reader's primary anxiety (confirmation + reframe) before delivering design inspiration, then moves through practical execution (colour, shape, salon guidance, grooming). The structure mirrors the reader's decision journey: first believe → then choose → then execute. Including the quiet luxury distinction H2 fulfils the cluster's internal linking requirement naturally and adds SEO depth that no competitor provides.

